node.text: Maravillosa
Beautyyyyy!

I’ll be honest: mercury retrograde has been rough for me. I’ve been processing a lot, questioning a lot, releasing a lot, feeling a lot. it’s all been good and necessary but very overwhelming, and I’ve been finding that it’s been easier for me to be in a funk of self-doubt that comes with navigating the unknown than it has been for me to be present to what is here now. and the one thing that never fails to bring me back to the present is gratitude. so. here’s a short list of what I’m grateful for in this moment:

I’m grateful for black femmes. I’m grateful for my ancestors. I’m grateful for sunny skies and cool water. I’m grateful for a partner who is willing to grow with and be challenged by me. I’m grateful for mangoes. I’m grateful for being a virgo. I’m grateful for my ability to know what I’m worth. I’m grateful for gold. I’m grateful for my blackness. & I’m grateful for all of you who are witnessing me in this moment. (thank you.) tell me what you’re grateful for today. ✨ (shoutout to @lexijohnnyhair for giving me a new look today. I am in love!)
My best friends, the universe being on time all the time, sunshine, Hoggie snuggles, mangoes, water, @nolaskinsentials , meditation, and remembering who I am. ❤️
Grateful for that Bey quote i see up on your wall! Grateful for our ability to bare it all and the platforms which allow us to share with other women.
@bretteliza *turned me on to you!
Grateful for my BAE @kimcandikaalford who turned me in to you and always keeps me honest!
I am thankful for the I love I have with my sisters, my brother & my mom & dad ♥️
I’m grateful for life 🙏🏽
I’m grateful for peace of mind.
@elianabanana__  follow this gorgeous soul!!!
Grateful for an honest partner who has helped me recently see how I am not living in my truth
@lexijohnnyhair 🥰 You are magic.
@amanthus so glad you connected us!
@amanthus 🙏💖
By the way shout to one of my Awesome Client for messaging me to connect with you. @amanthus 🙌😘
@saraclarkyoga thanks love!
@evyan.whitney pardon the typos😭🤗🥰
I feel you sis! And attitude of gratitude always balances out the intensity if life and in this case Mercury retrograde. Thanks for the reminder. Hair is looking good!
I’m grateful for my girl @na_talie29 💕

Finding your page somehow through cosmic black magical love is what I’m grateful for. Also, for learning self-love and self-care in my lowest moments. Learning to ride my highs with grace and humility. Digging into my bones. Cheers to the retrograde and 🌙eclipse
Grateful for this post on early Sunday rainy morning while drinking my black coffee ☕️ ( very very grateful for that ) helloz and thank you from London 🇬🇧

You’re stunning as always, Ev’Yan! I’ve been following you online since I read your interview on Black Girl with Long Hair; loved your ethic and vibe and I continue to encourage people to seek you out for all of the sexual liberation advice and resources you share. So first, I’m grateful for you and other folks like you working to empower POC. Thank you ❤️. These days I’m also grateful for spaces I can call my own. Spaces to live, work, retreat, and just be.

For the penetration of the Sun. For deep sleep. For cold water when it’s so damn hot outside. For the wisdom of the desert. For friends that pick you up from the airport. For your work in the world. For my mother. For being touched by hands that listen and respond and respect. For coconut oil. For this inhale.

I am grateful for the new striped tank top that I love and that my partner always compliments whenever I wear it. I’m grateful that it’s Saturday and I had a calm work week. I’m grateful for the friends I’m making at the gym, for banana pancakes, for lattes, and for creative writing. ❤️
@chynnadollyogi 💕💕💕
I’m grateful for spending time with the lovely @jewels_pena today ❤️💕
Awww yes my sister did your hair!😍🙌🏾
Yesssssss Virgo. We are some deep folks
Why are your eyebrows so perfect.😢
Gorgeous 💜💜💜🔥🔥🔥
Maravillosa
Beautyyyyy!
